    <item>
      <title>On Clearing Prices in Matching Markets: A Simple Characterization without Duality</title>
      <link>/post/market-clearing/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Dec 2019 16:19:55 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/market-clearing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/pdf/1912.00786.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;This&lt;/a&gt; is a note about market-clearing prices in a matching market, where we prove that: (1) the space of market-clearing prices is convex; (2) the space of market-learning prices is closed under element-wise maximum and minimum operations; (3) any market-clearing prices induce all maximum matchings.  We prove these claims using elementary mathematics, instead of using the classical yet opaque approach that relies on duality of linear programming.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
